cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with emotional state categorization from speech signals, which falls under the domain of sound processing. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper proposes a multistage categorization strategy and applies machine learning to the emotional speech corpora, which involves natural language processing and computational linguistics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper applies machine learning techniques to emotional speech categorization and compares the performance of the proposed system with human performance. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a psychologically inspired computational model for emotional state categorization from speech signals, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper compares the performance of the proposed system with human performance and uncovers some differences between machine and humans in terms of emotional state recognition from speech, which involves human-computer interaction.
